title: Michigan State forward Goins has sports hernia surgery
text:
Michigan State redshirt freshman forward Goins to miss 6 weeks after sports hernia surgery THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   8:04   8:04   
Subjects: 
Michigan (860) 

EAST LANSING, Michigan â€” Michigan State redshirt freshman forward Kenny Goins is expected to miss six weeks due to a sports hernia injury. 
The school says Wednesday in a release that surgery to repair the hernia was successful. 
The 6-foot-6 Goins joined the Spartans as a walk-on before the 2014-15 season. 
Goins is from Troy in suburban Detroit.
